<TABLE BORDER="0" CELLBORDER="1" CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="4">
  <TR><TD BGCOLOR="#ffb3b3" WIDTH="150"><B>Conclusion</B></TD></TR>
  <TR><TD ALIGN="left" WIDTH="150">We hold that once a sale and liquidation<BR ALIGN='left'/>meets the technical requirements of §<BR ALIGN='left'/>368(a)(1)(D), it can be reclassified as<BR ALIGN='left'/>a Section D reorganization without the<BR ALIGN='left'/>necessity of the Government showing that<BR ALIGN='left'/>the transaction was structured as a sale<BR ALIGN='left'/>and liquidation to receive more<BR ALIGN='left'/>favorable tax treatment.</TD></TR>
</TABLE>
>]
